MBOMBELA - Mpumalanga's Community Safety Department has been unable to pay its service providers on time. This has led to employees, including security companies guarding hospitals, not being paid. The department says it's been experiencing budgetary problems since last December. READ: Growing concerns over hospital safety It says a plan has been made to pay affected service providers by this coming weekend. Department spokesperson Moeti Mmusi said that by 1 February all the security providers giving services to the department will be paid. Mmusi said the security situation for healthcare providers has greatly improved. The department spokesperson was unable to comment on whether security guards would be equipped with guns.